ARTICLE XX
CHILDCARE

A. PARTICIPATION IN CAMPUS CHILDCARE PROGRAMS
SRs shall be eligible to participate in a campus childcare program, if any,
including subsidies and other financial assistance, in accordance with the
provisions of each location’s childcare program. Each location shall post
information regarding its childcare program on the web.
B. SYSTEM-WIDE CHILDCARE REIMBURSEMENT PROGRAM
1. Upon ratification of the contract, each eligible SR shall receive up to $6000
per quarter or $9000 per semester for childcare expenses incurred during
the SR’s appointment period.
2. Eligible SRs shall receive full tuition subsidies at UC-affiliated childcare
programs.
3. An eligible SR is a registered student with at least a 25% SR appointment
during the academic year who has (a) qualified dependent(s). For the
purposes of this program, qualified dependents shall include minors in the
care of the SR.
4. The University shall post the system-wide childcare enrollment form
on-line.
5. Eligible SRs shall have access to emergency walk-in childcare services
available on campus.

C. DEPCARE PARTICIPATION
All SRs who do not qualify for Dependent Healthcare Premium Remissions per
Article XX shall be entitled to participate in the UC Dependent Care
Reimbursement Program. The terms of this plan shall be determined by UC in
accordance with Internal Revenue Service regulations.
